cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on using supervised learning techniques for event abstraction in process mining. The paper discusses the use of feature vector representations of events and Condition Random Fields for event abstraction. These techniques are commonly used in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of event logs, which are commonly used in the field of databases (cs.DB). The paper's focus on process discovery and conformance checking suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
